===================================================================================
TRIP_SEARCHRQ API - XML REQUEST AND RESPONSE SAMPLES FOR YOUR USE CASE
VERSION: 4.5.0
===================================================================================

SUMMARY OF YOUR REQUIREMENT:
  Input:  Flight Number, Departure Date/Time, Airline Code (+ optional airport)
  Output: Passengers with Phone Numbers
  API:    Trip_SearchRQ v4.5.0 (SOAP-based XML Web Service)
  View:   TripSearchBasic (recommended for your needs)

===================================================================================
SAMPLE 1: BASIC REQUEST - Simple Flight Search with All Required Parameters
===================================================================================

REQUEST DESCRIPTION:
  Find all active passengers on Etihad Airways flight ET0001 departing 
  from JFK on 2016-12-20 at 07:00 UTC.

XML REQUEST:
============

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Trip_SearchRQ Version="4.5.0" 
               xmlns:ns2="http://webservices.sabre.com/sabreXML/2003/07" 
               xmlns="http://webservices.sabre.com/triprecord">
    <ReadRequests>
        <ReservationReadRequest>
            <FlightCriteria>
                <Flight>
                    <FlightNumber>0001</FlightNumber>
                    <DepartureAirport>JFK</DepartureAirport>
                    <DepartureDateTime Is="2016-12-20T07:00:00"/>
                    <AirlineCode>ET</AirlineCode>
                </Flight>
            </FlightCriteria>
            <PosCriteria AirlineCode="ET"/>
            <ReturnOptions ViewName="TripSearchBasic" 
                          MaxItemsReturned="800" 
                          ResponseFormat="STL"
                          SearchType="ACTIVE"/>
        </ReservationReadRequest>
    </ReadRequests>
</Trip_SearchRQ>

EXPECTED RESPONSE BEHAVIOR:
  - Returns all active PNRs with passengers on this flight
  - Automatically includes: HEADER, NAME, PHONE, PASSENGERDETAILS
  - Phone numbers will be in CustomerContact/Phone elements
  - Each PNR shows passenger details

===================================================================================
SAMPLE 2: REQUEST WITH TIME RANGE - For Flexible Departure Time Matching
===================================================================================

REQUEST DESCRIPTION:
  Find all passengers on American Airlines flight 288 departing from 
  Frankfurt (FRA) on 2016-12-22 between 12:00 UTC and 13:30 UTC.

XML REQUEST:
============

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Trip_SearchRQ Version="4.5.0" 
               xmlns:ns2="http://webservices.sabre.com/sabreXML/2003/07" 
               xmlns="http://webservices.sabre.com/triprecord">
    <ReadRequests>
        <ReservationReadRequest>
            <FlightCriteria>
                <Flight>
                    <FlightNumber>288</FlightNumber>
                    <DepartureAirport>FRA</DepartureAirport>
                    <DepartureDateTime After="2016-12-22T12:00:00" 
                                       Before="2016-12-22T13:30:00"/>
                    <AirlineCode>AA</AirlineCode>
                </Flight>
            </FlightCriteria>
            <PosCriteria AirlineCode="AA"/>
            <ReturnOptions ViewName="TripSearchBasic" 
                          MaxItemsReturned="800" 
                          ResponseFormat="STL"
                          SearchType="ACTIVE"/>
        </ReservationReadRequest>
    </ReadRequests>
</Trip_SearchRQ>

KEY DIFFERENCES:
  - Uses After/Before instead of Is for time range matching
  - DepartureDateTime specifies a range instead of exact time
  - Matches any departure between 12:00 and 13:30

===================================================================================
SAMPLE 3: REQUEST WITH ARRIVAL CRITERIA - For Multi-leg Flight Matching
===================================================================================

REQUEST DESCRIPTION:
  Find passengers on Ethiopian Airlines flight 1 from JFK to AUH departing
  on 2016-12-20 after 07:00 UTC and arriving before 2016-12-21 10:00 UTC.

XML REQUEST:
============

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Trip_SearchRQ Version="4.5.0" 
               xmlns:ns2="http://webservices.sabre.com/sabreXML/2003/07" 
               xmlns="http://webservices.sabre.com/triprecord">
    <ReadRequests>
        <ReservationReadRequest>
            <FlightCriteria>
                <Flight>
                    <FlightNumber>0001</FlightNumber>
                    <DepartureAirport>JFK</DepartureAirport>
                    <ArrivalAirport>AUH</ArrivalAirport>
                    <DepartureDateTime After="2016-12-20T07:00:00"/>
                    <ArrivalDateTime Before="2016-12-21T10:00:00"/>
                    <AirlineCode>ET</AirlineCode>
                </Flight>
            </FlightCriteria>
            <PosCriteria AirlineCode="ET"/>
            <ReturnOptions ViewName="TripSearchBasic" 
                          MaxItemsReturned="800" 
                          ResponseFormat="STL"
                          SearchType="ACTIVE"/>
        </ReservationReadRequest>
    </ReadRequests>
</Trip_SearchRQ>

KEY DIFFERENCES:
  - Includes ArrivalAirport for additional matching criteria
  - Uses ArrivalDateTime to filter by arrival time
  - More restrictive search criteria (narrows results)

===================================================================================
SAMPLE 4: REQUEST WITH ADDITIONAL SUBJECT AREAS - For More Details
===================================================================================

REQUEST DESCRIPTION:
  Same flight search but explicitly requesting additional data including
  itinerary details along with basic passenger and phone information.

XML REQUEST:
============

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Trip_SearchRQ Version="4.5.0" 
               xmlns:ns2="http://webservices.sabre.com/sabreXML/2003/07" 
               xmlns="http://webservices.sabre.com/triprecord">
    <ReadRequests>
        <ReservationReadRequest>
            <FlightCriteria>
                <Flight>
                    <FlightNumber>0001</FlightNumber>
                    <DepartureAirport>JFK</DepartureAirport>
                    <DepartureDateTime Is="2016-12-20T07:00:00"/>
                    <AirlineCode>ET</AirlineCode>
                </Flight>
            </FlightCriteria>
            <PosCriteria AirlineCode="ET"/>
            <ReturnOptions ViewName="TripSearchBlob" 
                          MaxItemsReturned="800" 
                          ResponseFormat="STL"
                          SearchType="ACTIVE">
                <SubjectAreas>
                    <SubjectArea>HEADER</SubjectArea>
                    <SubjectArea>NAME</SubjectArea>
                    <SubjectArea>PHONE</SubjectArea>
                    <SubjectArea>PASSENGERDETAILS</SubjectArea>
                    <SubjectArea>ITINERARY</SubjectArea>
                    <SubjectArea>FQTV</SubjectArea>
                </SubjectAreas>
            </ReturnOptions>
        </ReservationReadRequest>
    </ReadRequests>
</Trip_SearchRQ>

KEY DIFFERENCES FROM SAMPLE 1:
  - ViewName changed from "TripSearchBasic" to "TripSearchBlob"
  - Explicitly lists SubjectAreas (these define what data is returned)
  - Includes ITINERARY and FQTV (Frequent Flyer) data
  - Response will be larger but more comprehensive

AVAILABLE SUBJECT AREAS:
  HEADER                = PNR header, record locator, creation date
  NAME                  = Passenger name (already in TripSearchBasic)
  PHONE                 = Phone number(s) (already in TripSearchBasic)
  PASSENGERDETAILS      = Extended passenger info (already in TripSearchBasic)
  FQTV                  = Frequent Flyer numbers
  ADDRESS               = Passenger address
  RECEIVED              = "Received from" information
  DKNUMBER              = Agency customer number
  CUST_INSIGHT_PROFILE  = Customer profile data
  ITINERARY             = Full itinerary details
  REMARKS               = PNR remarks

